As more information of the fluxes is obtained, various technologies such as Electrochromic Shift (ECS) and fluorescent probes are gushed to boost CO2 fixation and yields of biofuels and chemicals from microalgae. The non-invasive and continuous properties of an index in live microalgal cell are credible to reveal the nature of cellular metabolism. ECS signals have been proposed for a long time to reflect conditions of energy and pigment in algal cells [139]. ECS represents a shift in the absorption spectra of some photosynthetic pigments that are induced by electric field in light-dependent reaction. Normally, ECS is expressed as follows:11ECS=(→F,→F2),\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
